A typical example?
In a weekend home that is not heated regularly, latex mattresses are not well suited as they take much longer to “get warm.”
In addition, they are significantly heavier than ordinary polyurethane mattresses.
And - they should be turned regularly.
For if they do not have enough ventilation canals in the core and still lie on a solid plate, moisture is stuck: so it is not excluded that mold is formed underneath them.
