Finally, in the last days of October, Merkel comes out again with a clear position, calling for a reform of the agreements of the European Union to enable the rescue of a country and at the same time to obligate private lenders to bear a part of the costs.
This position was interpreted as anti-European as it propelled the Irish crisis and everything that followed.
